description.p:
A robot system, comprising:
an arm mechanism that is articulated;
a parallel link mechanism including
a fixed part mounted to a distal part of the arm mechanism, and
a movable part mounted to the fixed part via multiple parallel links, the movable part being movable with respect to the fixed part;
an end effector mounted to the movable part, the end effector performing a task on a task object;
a detector for detecting a position relationship or orientation relationship between the movable part and the task object; and
a control device controlling the arm mechanism and the parallel link mechanism,
in the task of the end effector, the control device adjusts the posture of the end effector by moving the parallel link mechanism based on the detection result of the detector.
